edu.udel.cis.taschd.course

Class CourseInstancePool

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.udel.cis.taschd.course.CourseInstancePool

  • public class CourseInstancePool
extends java.lang.Object

    The CourseInstancePool class is responsible for managing CourseInstance Objects e.g., obtaining all CourseInstances as a list. It hides the details on the internal representation of course instance objects.

    CourseInstancePool is a Collection of CourseInstances.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CourseInstancePool

        public CourseInstancePool(java.util.Collection<CourseInstance> courseInstancePool)
        Constructs a new CourseInstancePool from the given collection of CourseInstances. The new CourseInstancePool will not keep any reference to the given Collection, hence subsequent modifications to the collection will not affect the new CourseInstancePool. The new CourseInstancePool may keep references to the member CourseInstances of the collection, but since CourseInstances are immutable, this fact should be invisible to the client. The internal representation may differ from the organization of the collection, in that CourseInstances will be ordered and duplicates removed. The given Collection will not be modified.
        Parameters:
        courseInstancePool - any Collection of non-null CourseAssistants that will be used to build the new CourseAssistantSet.
